Roles & Responsibilities
Job Description
Performance clinical duties such as
- Medication management and medication packing;
- Post-surgical wound management;
- Insertion of nasogastric tube;
- Care of Percutaneous Endoscopic Gastrostomy (PEG) tube and dressing;
- Wound management (Stage I to Stage IV wounds711);
- Urinary catheter care and change of female urinary catheters;
- Tracheostomy care and dressing;
- Stoma care – colostomy and ileostomy care;
- Care of nephrostomy tube and dressing;
- Assistance with bowel elimination (e.g. enema or insertion of suppositories, as ordered by a physician; and
- Post-procedural medication administration, as ordered by medical personnel (Only applicable for clients who are not already enrolled in the centre’s day care programmes and are living alone or unable to take medication on their own.)
Precept new staff in clinical matters
Assist in Audit
Job Requirement
Minimum a Diploma in nursing.
Registered nurse with SNB.
2-3 years of relevant experience

Roles & Responsibilities
As a Staff Nurse, you will:
join a team of well-trained professional staff to administer personalised and quality person-centred care in the inpatient wards;
provide professional nursing care, educate patients and their family and perform related duties as required;
supervise and coach a team of nurses to provide optimal care and service to patients;
be provided with opportunities for training and development.
Job Requirements
Hold a valid registration with the Singapore Nursing Board;
Possess a Diploma or Bachelor Degree in Nursing educational qualification;
Able to work 3-rotating shifts and weekends.

Roles & Responsibilities
Perform nursing assessments of Dementia Clients during admission;
Involved in developing Individualised Care Plan for dementia Clients with other care team members;
Involved in multidisciplinary case discussion with the other care team members;
Conduct education and training for the dementia client’s caregiver as provides support as required;
Conduct in-service training sessions for the staff and volunteers; and
Oversee clients’ medical and nursing needs and maintains documentation of the Clients’ progress and outcomes of care provision.
Requirements :
· Singaporeans preferred
· Registered with the Singapore Nursing Board
· Minimum Nitec in Nursing
· Highly motivated & ability working in a team

